# Passenger Safety

Safety is the cornerstone of Waggle's operations. Our dogs are more than passengers—they're family members entrusted to our care. This document outlines our comprehensive safety framework, from vehicle requirements to emergency protocols.

## Vehicle Requirements

All Waggle vehicles must meet these standards before they can accept their first passenger. We conduct quarterly inspections to ensure continued compliance.

### Climate Control

Temperature management is critical for dog safety. Dogs can suffer heatstroke in as little as 15 minutes in a hot vehicle.

- **AC must reach 68°F within 5 minutes** - Dogs can't wait in hot cars
- **Rear vents required** - Direct airflow to passenger area
- **Temperature monitoring** - In-car sensor reports to app every 30 seconds
- **Auto-cancel in extreme temps** - >85°F or <32°F triggers hold
- **Heating requirements** - Must maintain 65°F minimum in winter conditions
- **Window tinting** - Rear windows must have 35% or darker tint for heat reduction

#### Temperature Response Protocol

| Interior Temp | System Response | Driver Action Required |
|---------------|-----------------|------------------------|
| 68-72°F | Optimal | None |
| 73-77°F | Warning | Increase AC |
| 78-82°F | Alert to human | Pull over, assess |
| 83-85°F | Ride paused | Find shade, run AC |
| >85°F | Emergency | Evacuate, call support |
| <40°F | Warning | Increase heat |
| <32°F | Ride paused | Warm up vehicle |

### Restraint Systems

Proper restraint prevents injury during sudden stops and keeps dogs from distracting drivers. Our requirements are based on crash test data and veterinary recommendations.

| Dog Size | Weight Range | Requirement | Approved Products |
|----------|--------------|-------------|-------------------|
| XS | <10 lbs | Secured carrier in seat | Sleepypod, Kurgo |
| Small | 10-20 lbs | Carrier or car seat with tether | PetSafe, K&H |
| Medium | 20-50 lbs | Seat belt harness attachment | Kurgo, Ruffwear |
| Large | 50-100 lbs | Cargo area with barrier | Various barriers |
| XL | >100 lbs | SUV/van only, cargo area | Heavy-duty barriers |

#### Harness Specifications

All harnesses must meet these crash-test standards:

- **Certified crash-tested** at 30 mph impact
- **Three-point attachment** distributing force across chest
- **Quick-release buckle** for emergency exit
- **Reflective trim** for visibility
- **Chew-resistant webbing** (we learned this the hard way)

### Cleanliness Standards

A clean vehicle is a healthy vehicle. Dogs are sensitive to residual allergens and chemicals from previous passengers.

- Vehicles cleaned between each ride (minimum 10 minutes)
- Lint rollers provided (fur management)
- Waterproof seat covers mandatory
- No strong air fresheners (sensitive noses)
- Enzyme cleaner for accidents (not chemical deodorizers)
- Paw wipes available for muddy passengers
- Emergency cleanup kit in every vehicle

#### Cleaning Checklist

| Task | Frequency | Verification |
|------|-----------|--------------|
| Surface wipe-down | Every ride | Photo upload |
| Fur removal | Every ride | Photo upload |
| Deep clean | Weekly | In-person inspection |
| Allergen treatment | Monthly | Certificate required |
| Seat cover replacement | As needed | Receipt submission |

### Vehicle Inspection Requirements

Before onboarding, and quarterly thereafter:

1. **Mechanical safety** - Brakes, tires, suspension
2. **Climate system** - AC/heat response time test
3. **Restraint anchors** - Load testing of attachment points
4. **Cleanliness baseline** - Allergen testing
5. **Cargo area** - Barrier integrity, escape prevention
6. **Windows and doors** - Child locks functional, window limits set

## Driver Certification

Our drivers are the front line of passenger safety. Waggle drivers complete more training than standard rideshare drivers, with specialized modules on canine behavior and emergency response.

### Initial Certification

Drivers must complete:

1. **Online course** (2 hours) - Dog behavior basics
   - Canine body language reading
   - Stress signals and calming techniques
   - Breed-specific considerations
   - Common medical conditions to recognize

2. **In-person training** (4 hours) - Handling, safety, treats
   - Vehicle setup and restraint systems
   - Safe dog loading/unloading procedures
   - Treat dispensing techniques
   - Emergency scenario role-play

3. **Test ride** - With Waggle QA dog (currently Buster)
   - Real-world driving with live passenger
   - Evaluated by experienced trainer
   - Scored on safety, comfort, and dog happiness

4. **Background check** - Standard rideshare + animal cruelty screening
   - Criminal background (7-year history)
   - Driving record review
   - Animal cruelty database check
   - Reference verification

5. **Annual recertification** - Updated training + new features
   - Refresher on safety protocols
   - New feature training
   - Performance review based on ratings
   - Medical condition updates

### Driver Performance Metrics

| Metric | Target | Minimum | Consequence Below Minimum |
|--------|--------|---------|---------------------------|
| Safety score | 4.9/5 | 4.5/5 | Retraining required |
| On-time arrival | >95% | 90% | Warning |
| Treat satisfaction | >90% | 80% | Review |
| Incident-free rides | >99.5% | 98% | Suspension pending review |
| Customer rating | 4.8/5 | 4.5/5 | Performance plan |

### Specialized Certifications

